(X,d)
 A,B,C
X
\mathrm{dist}(A,B) = \inf \{d(x,y) \mid x\in A , y \in B \}
\mathrm{dist}(A,C) \le \mathrm{dist}(A,B)+ \mathrm{dist}(B,C)
d(a,b) \le d(a,c) +  d(c,b) 
d(\{a\},\{b\}) \neq 0
a \neq b
d(\{a\},\{a,b\})=d(\{a,b\},\{b\})=0
\mathbb{R}
d
A = [0,1], B = [1,2], C = [2,3]
\operatorname{dist}(A,B) = \operatorname{dist}(B,C) = 0
\operatorname{dist}(A,C) = 1
d(1,2) = 1
